8908","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/382851.html?thread=19521923#t19521923","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/382851.html?thread=19521923#t19521923","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/382851.html?thread=19521923#t19521923","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2322631","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/MeroVFX","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19521923,"talkid":76257,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/382851.html?thread=19521923#t19521923","upictitle":"David Incio: pic#122391259","article":"Two months ago i finally got the opportunity to buy the book \"Histories of the Seven Kingdoms\" (portuguese version) wich brings us the three tales of Dunk & Egg. Until this summer we've only had the first tale translated in your \"A RRetrospective\" book wich i also had bought earlier this year. <br />Maybe i'll have to wait some years to read the two prequels \"princess and the queen\" and \"the rogue prince\", but since you have so many fans in the Portuguese speaking 'world' that i'm praying to all the seven gods that your Portuguese publisher could bring us \"The World of Ice and Fire\" soon after the original comes out.<br />I also know i shouldn't be demanding anything because the english readers waited probably more than i did, and as you can see i can write/read english but the portuguese translation by Mr.Jorge Candeias is very good, he has made an superb job.<br />With that said, i'd like to thank you, Great Maester Martin for bringing us this world of fantasy, and if i should pray to R'hllor instead, just tell me because i realy want to read it all, and i can hardly wait! :)<br />Thank you for all<br />One of your Fans <br />- David Inácio -","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"September 9 2014, 20:36:10 UTC"